The impervious surface data were derived from the National Land Cover Database (NLCD) 2001 percent developed imperviousness data set, a product of the Multi-Resolution Land Characteristics Consortium (MRLC). The MRLC is a multi-agency cooperative effort to study land cover change. The NLCD 2001 is described at <http://www.mrlc.gov/nlcd2001.php>.</dct:description>         <dcat:keyword>united states</dcat:keyword>         <dcat:keyword>environmental impacts</dcat:keyword>
